panels.content:
# Throughput Trends

This dashboard display an overview of how throughput changes over time 
For each benchmark you can compare throughput metrics for a specific
number of terminals. You can also compare a throughput metric across 
different terminal values. Feel free to mix and match, but be warned
the charts can get overwhelming pretty fast.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  "time" AS "time",
  (metrics->>'throughput')::numeric AS "terminals = 1",
  git_commit_id
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("time") AND
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals}) AND
  terminals = 1 AND
  client_time = 60 AND
  git_branch = 'origin/master' AND
  wal_device = '$wal_device' AND
  max_connection_threads = 32
ORDER BY time

  (FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals ORDER BY time DESC) -
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals ORDER BY time ASC)) / 
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals ORDER BY time ASC) * 100 AS "Change"
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("time") AND
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals}) AND
  client_time = 60 AND
  git_branch = 'origin/master'  AND
  wal_device = '$wal_device' AND
  max_connection_threads = 32
